o be king over his people, over Israel: now therefore hearken thou unto the voice of the words of the LORD.","year":-1079},{"id":"recIfAY7bYbEw9a7d","ref":"1Sam.15.2","text":"Thus saith the LORD of hosts, I remember that which Amalek did to Israel, how he laid wait for him in the way, when he came up from Egypt.","year":-1079},{"id":"recd3GZPkHusGnKo3","ref":"1Sam.15.3","text":"Now go and smite Amalek, and utterly destroy all that they have, and spare them not; but slay both man and woman, infant and suckling, ox and sheep, camel and ass.","year":-1079},{"id":"recHkIiGwMHnY4Mfy","ref":"1Sam.15.4","text":"And Saul gathered the people together, and numbered them in Telaim, two hundred thousand footmen, and ten thousand men of Judah.","year":-1079},{"id":"recpsczIxCGDMEwI4","ref":"1Sam.15.5","text":"And Saul came to a city of Amalek, and laid wait in the valley.","year":-1079},{"id":"recEJQ8y9Dgef5sOp","ref":"1Sam.15.6","text":"And Saul said unto the Kenites, Go, depart, get you down from among the Amalekites, lest I destroy you with them: for ye shewed kindness to all the children of Israel, when they came up out of Egypt. So the Kenites departed from among the Amalekites.","year":-1079},{"id":"rec9NkVZc1ECkPals","ref":"1Sam.15.7","text":"And Saul smote the Amalekites from Havilah until thou comest to Shur, that is over against Egypt.","year":-1079},{"id":"recBk24HxgYxnDXhX","ref":"1Sam.15.8","text":"And he took Agag the king of the Amalekites alive, and utterly destroyed all the people with the edge of the sword.","year":-1079}]}
